## Chapter 2. File Hierarchy

Directories divided by its functionality.

/ - root directory
/sbin - executable files
/bin - executable files
/lib - libraries
/etc - configuration (unshareable)
/var - variable data
/boot - files of the boot loader (unshareable)
/tmp - temporary files
/srv - data provided by services
/usr - secondary hierarchy (shareable)
/opt - additional software (shareable)
/dev - device files
/media - mount point for removable media
/mnt - mount point for mounting a filesystem temporarily

optional:
------------------------------------------------
/home - user home directories
/lib<qualifier>	- alternate format essential shared libraries
/root - home directory for the root user
------------------------------------------------
/run - temporary files across system runnings [Data relevant to running processes]

